<subSubSection id="5F8E8625CC1B118094171AA9DEB84E5A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="2F4B832AA7AE46B8661591A71ECA4C33" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A3A728408082D3F6685D1EEAD30BEB37" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Slender twining annual herb, nearly glabrous in all parts. Leaves petiolate, mostly 3-5.5 
<normalizedToken id="D96A352D4169B1D9BE5D85AFCA297EC6" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-4.5 cm, ovate or shallowly 3-lobed, cordate with rounded to obtuse auricles, apex shortly acuminate, mucronate, adaxially thinly pubescent or glabrous; petioles 1.5-5 cm. Inflorescence of long pedunculate axillary umbelliform cymes with 2-5 flowers; peduncles 2-10 cm; bracteoles tiny, triangular, caducous; pedicels 5-15 mm; sepals subequal, oblong-obovate with broad scarious margins, rounded and mucronate, usually glabrous but occasionally ciliate; outer sepals 3.5-6 mm; inner sepals c. 1 mm longer; corolla 1.5-2.5 cm long, funnel-shaped, pink with a dark centre, glabrous, limb 1.5-1.75 cm diam., unlobed, sometimes dentate. Capsules 3-4 
<normalizedToken id="B14C233A9E3913822DC2E27D3C00581F" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4 mm, ovoid, exceeding sepals, glabrous or thinly pilose, the slender style somewhat persistent; seeds 3-3.5 
<normalizedToken id="1EF4BF8ECC3F6DE56A02AAE222444B51" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.5 mm, ellipsoid, dark brown, glabrous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
